    <!-- Widescreen patcher -->
    <system:String x:Key="PATCHES">Patch</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="APPLY_WIDESCREEN_PATCH">Apply widescreen patch</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="WIDESCREEN_PATCH">Widescreen patch</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="ASPECT_RATIO">Aspect ratio</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="ASPECT_RATIO_WIDTH">Width px (e.g. 1920)</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="ASPECT_RATIO_HEIGHT">Height px (e.g. 1080)</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="CAMERA_DISTANCE">Camera distance</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="APPLY_CAMERA_DISTANCE">Change the camera distance</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="CAMERA_DISTANCE_FROM_LARA">Distance between the camera and Lara</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="CAMERA_DISTANCE_HELP_TEXT">In classic Tomb Raider games, the camera follows Lara at a distance of one and a half blocks, where one block is a square with a side length of 1024 units. You can use this setting to increase or decrease this value. If you choose the "Custom" option, enter the value in units, not in number of blocks.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="CUSTOM_DISTANCE">Custom distance</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="CAMERA_DISTANCE_PRESET_ONE_BLOCK">1 block</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="CAMERA_DISTANCE_PRESET_ONE_AND_HALF_BLOCKS">1 and a half blocks</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="CAMERA_DISTANCE_PRESET_TWO_BLOCKS">2 blocks</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="CAMERA_DISTANCE_PRESET_TWO_AND_HALF_BLOCKS">2 and a half blocks</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="CAMERA_DISTANCE_PRESET_THREE_BLOCKS">3 blocks</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="CAMERA_DISTANCE_PRESET_CUSTOM">Custom</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="FOV">Field of view</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="APPLY_FOV_CORRECTION">Apply field of view correction</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="FOV_HELP_TEXT">In classic Tomb Raider games, the horizontal field of view is approximately 65°. Applying the widescreen patch without this fix widens the image but keeps the original field of view designed for 4:3, which may make the camera feel unnaturally narrow and claustrophobic. Enter the screen width in pixels used in the game setup (e.g. 1920) to calculate the correction.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="SCREEN_WIDTH">Horizontal resolution</system:String>
